For Raila, Peter Kenneth remains the preferred running mate with 36.6 per cent of respondents saying he would be the best choice. He is followed by Kalonzo Musyoka with 10.5 per cent support and Martha Karua with 9.8 per cent. In January, 27.3 per cent of respondents said Kenneth would be the best running mate for Raila. The Radio Africa survey of 3,152 respondents was conducted by computer-assisted telephone interviewing between February 1 and 5 across all 47 counties. It carries a 1.75 per cent margin of error.